title: Influence of Intermediate States of the Fissionable Nucleus Th-232 on Mass and Kinetic Energy Distributions of Fragments

Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.7, p.475 (1968)

x4freetext: English Translation of Yf
Influence of Intermediate States of the Fissionable
Nucleus Th-232 on Mass and Kinetic Energy
Distributions of Fragments
Van De Graaff
Proton-Tritium Reaction
Deuteron-Deuterium Reaction
Coincidence Between Fragments
Silicon Detector
Mass of Fission Fragments was Calculated According
To the Formula  Mh=a*El/(EL+EH).
Here a=233 - Mass-Number of Fissible Neucleus
El and Eh - Kinetic Energy Measured
For Light and Heavy Fragments,Respectively
Mh-Mass of Heavy Fission Fragment
Mass and Energy Distributions
Of Fragments at the Fission of U-235 by Thermal
Neutrons were Used on the Graduation of Energy Scale
Of the Analyser
When Grossing to the Masses of Primary Fragments
In Value Mh was Introduced the Correction on Emission
Of Prompt Neutrons by Fission Fragments.It was Supposed
That the Dependence Nu(M) Of Average Neutron-Number
From the Masses of Fission Fragments For Fission
Of Th-232 by Neutrons with Energy En=1.65 MeV
Is Similar Nu(M) For Fission of U-233 by Thermal
Neutrons. The Normalization of Curve Nu(M) Was Produced
On the Value Nu=2.08 - Average Neutron-Number
For Fission of Th-232 by Neutrons with Energy 1.6 MeV.
Errors are not Specified
Data are Given by Authors.
Compiled at the Centre - Cjd

014,Introduced

Iso-Quant Into Reaction Converted
San 014 Deleted As not Containing any New
Data Records in Comparison to San 002 - 007
M.M. Subent 8 : Reaction and Data Units
Were Corrected
